  <static seed="137" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring500.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{3x^{3}-27x}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>3x\mathopen{}\left(x+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(x-3\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The first thing to observe is that <m>3x</m> is common to both 
terms; once we have factored this out, what remains is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {3x^{3}-27x} \amp  = 3x({x}^2-9)\\
                            \amp  = 3x({x}^2-3^2)\\
                            \amp  = {3x\mathopen{}\left(x+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(x-3\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
